In an ATM System, which would be a non-functional requirement?
The interface should be physically robust and hard wearing
Customer can view their account balance.
Customer can select an amount to withdraw.
Cash must be ejected for the customer.
Correct. This is a constraint on the performance of the interface, not an actual function the system performs.The others are simple, yet essential functional activities youd expect from an ATM and so, are functional activities.



The correct answer is The interface should be physically robust and hard wearing. This is a constraint on the performance of the interface, not an actual function the system performs.The others are simple, yet essential functional activities youd expect from an ATM and so, are functional activities.
